TITLE: Setting network binding capability for Mattermost binary (Shell)
DESCRIPTION: This command sets the `CAP_NET_BIND_SERVICE` capability for the Mattermost binary. This allows the binary to bind to ports lower than 1024, such as port 80 or 443, if TLS is set up on the Mattermost server. It requires `sudo` for elevated privileges and the `setcap` utility.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mattermost/docs/blob/master/source/upgrade/upgrading-mattermost-server.rst#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: sh
CODE:
```
sudo setcap cap_net_bind_service=+ep ./mattermost/bin/mattermost
```

