TITLE: Modify Posts Table Columns (MySQL)
DESCRIPTION: This SQL snippet modifies the `FileIds` and `Props` columns in the `Posts` table. `FileIds` is modified to `text` and `Props` is modified to `JSON`. These changes are part of the v6.0 database schema migrations. Combining the queries limits the time taken to that of a single query of that type.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mattermost/docs/blob/master/source/deploy/server/prepare-mattermost-mysql-database.rst#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
ALTER TABLE Posts MODIFY COLUMN FileIds text, MODIFY COLUMN Props JSON;
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Adding a new column to the reactions table - PostgreSQL
DESCRIPTION: This SQL statement adds a new column `channelid` to the `reactions` table if it doesn't already exist. The column is of type `varchar(26)` and is set to `NOT NULL` with a default value of an empty string. This statement is intended to be run before upgrading to Mattermost v7.1. Adding `IF NOT EXISTS` prevents errors if the column already exists.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mattermost/docs/blob/master/source/upgrade/prepare-to-upgrade-mattermost.rst#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
ALTER TABLE reactions ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS channelid varchar(26) NOT NULL DEFAULT '';
```

