TITLE: Loading Custom Configuration Defaults via Environment Variable
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to load custom configuration defaults using the MM_CUSTOM_DEFAULTS_PATH environment variable. This variable should point to a JSON file containing the custom configuration defaults. This configuration applies only if the values are not already present in the current server configuration.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mattermost/docs/blob/master/source/configure/environment-variables.rst#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: Shell
CODE:
```
MM_CUSTOM_DEFAULTS_PATH=custom.json
```

