TITLE: Fixing Websocket 403 errors - NGINX
DESCRIPTION: This configuration snippet shows how to configure NGINX to correctly handle WebSocket connections for Mattermost, preventing 403 errors caused by failing cross-origin checks. It ensures the `Host` header is dynamically set and that `AllowCorsFrom` in `config.json` is properly configured.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mattermost/docs/blob/master/source/deploy/server/setup-nginx-proxy.rst#_snippet_25

LANGUAGE: text
CODE:
```
location ~ /api/v[0-9]+/(users/)?websocket$ {
  proxy_pass            http://backend;
  (...)
  proxy_set_header      Host $host;
  proxy_set_header      X-Forwarded-For $remote_addr;
}
```

