TITLE: Configuring Rate Limiting by HTTP Header in config.json
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to configure rate limiting by HTTP header in Mattermost's `config.json` file. The `RateLimitSettings.VaryByHeader` setting specifies the HTTP header field used to vary rate limiting API access. This is particularly useful when using a proxy, like NGINX (X-Real-IP) or AmazonELB (X-Forwarded-For).
SOURCE: https://github.com/mattermost/docs/blob/master/source/configure/rate-limiting-configuration-settings.rst#_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
".RateLimitSettings.VaryByHeader: \"\","
```

