TITLE: Resolving "Too many redirects" error - NGINX
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to resolve the "Too many redirects" error when running Mattermost in a sub-path by adding a specific location block to the NGINX configuration. This block handles HEAD requests with a 200 OK response to prevent redirection loops.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mattermost/docs/blob/master/source/deploy/server/setup-nginx-proxy.rst#_snippet_24

LANGUAGE: text
CODE:
```
location ~* ^/sub-path {
    client_max_body_size 250M;
    proxy_set_header Connection "";

    if ($request_method = HEAD) {
        return 200;
    }
}
```

