TITLE: PostgreSQL: Updating threadteamid with teamid from channels
DESCRIPTION: This SQL snippet updates the threadteamid column in the threads table with teamid values from the channels table in PostgreSQL. It joins the tables on channelid to retrieve the correct team ID for each thread, only updating rows where threadteamid is currently NULL.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mattermost/docs/blob/master/source/upgrade/important-upgrade-notes.rst#_snippet_32

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
UPDATE threads
SET threadteamid = channels.
  teamid
FROM channels
WHERE threads.threadteamid IS
  NULL
  AND channels.id = threads.
  channelid;
```

