TITLE: Creating Full-Text Indexes in PostgreSQL
DESCRIPTION: These SQL commands create full-text indexes on the `posts` and `fileinfo` tables in the PostgreSQL database. They use the `gin` index type and the `to_tsvector` function to index the `message` and `content` columns, respectively, for efficient text search.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mattermost/docs/blob/master/source/deploy/manual-postgres-migration.rst#_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_posts_message_txt ON public.posts USING gin(to_tsvector('english', message));
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_fileinfo_content_txt ON public.fileinfo USING gin(to_tsvector('english', content));
```

