TITLE: Creating unique index on PropertyFields in PostgreSQL
DESCRIPTION: Creates a unique index named `idx_propertyfields_unique` on the `PropertyFields` table in PostgreSQL if it doesn't already exist. The index is on the `GroupID`, `TargetID`, and `Name` columns, and it only applies to rows where `DeleteAt` is 0, effectively indexing only non-deleted property fields for uniqueness. This enforces uniqueness for property fields within a group and target.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mattermost/docs/blob/master/source/upgrade/important-upgrade-notes.rst#_snippet_13

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
 CREATE UNIQUE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_propertyfields_unique ON PropertyFields (GroupID, TargetID, Name) WHERE DeleteAt = 0;
```

