TITLE: Counting OAuth Access Data SQL
DESCRIPTION: This SQL query counts OAuth access tokens that are not associated with an OAuth application preference and have a valid session. It joins the `OAuthAccessData`, `Preferences`, and `Sessions` tables and filters for tokens where the preference is null.  This helps identify potentially orphaned or invalid access tokens.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mattermost/docs/blob/master/source/upgrade/important-upgrade-notes.rst#_snippet_24

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
 SELECT COUNT(o.`Token`)                                                                                                                                         
 FROM OAuthAccessData o                                                                                                                                          
 LEFT JOIN Preferences p ON o.                                                                                                                                   
   clientid = p.name                                                                                                                                             
   AND o.userid = p.userid                                                                                                                                       
   AND p.category = 'oauth_app'                                                                                                                                  
 INNER JOIN Sessions s ON o.token = s                                                                                                                            
   .token                                                                                                                                                        
 WHERE p.name IS NULL;
```

