TITLE: Creating Index on PropertyFields Table in MySQL
DESCRIPTION: This SQL snippet creates an index named `idx_propertyfields_create_at_id` on the `PropertyFields` table in MySQL if it does not already exist. The index is created on the `CreateAt` and `ID` columns to improve query performance for pagination. It uses a prepared statement to conditionally create the index, ensuring that it only runs if the index doesn't already exist.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mattermost/docs/blob/master/source/upgrade/important-upgrade-notes.rst#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
SET @preparedStatement = (SELECT IF(
    (
        SELECT COUNT(*) FROM INFORMATION_SCHEMA.STATISTICS
        WHERE table_name = 'PropertyFields'
        AND table_schema = DATABASE()
        AND index_name = 'idx_propertyfields_create_at_id'
    ) > 0,
    'SELECT 1',
    'CREATE INDEX idx_propertyfields_create_at_id ON PropertyFields(CreateAt, ID);'
));

PREPARE createIndexIfNotExists FROM @preparedStatement;
EXECUTE createIndexIfNotExists;
DEALLOCATE PREPARE createIndexIfNotExists;
```

