TITLE: Creating retentionidsfordeletion Table - PostgreSQL
DESCRIPTION: This SQL script creates the `retentionidsfordeletion` table in a PostgreSQL database. It defines the `id` as the primary key and creates an index on the `tablename` column for efficient querying. The `ids` column is defined as an array of VARCHAR(26) values. The `IF NOT EXISTS` clause ensures that the table is only created if it doesn't already exist.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mattermost/docs/blob/master/source/upgrade/important-upgrade-notes.rst#_snippet_19

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
CREATE TABLE
IF NOT EXISTS
retentionidsfordeletion(id
VARCHAR(26) PRIMARY KEY,
tablename VARCHAR(64),
ids VARCHAR(26) []);
CREATE INDEX
IF NOT EXISTS
idx_retentionidsfordeletion_tablename
ON retentionidsfordeletion(
tablename);
```

