TITLE: Count invalid Unicode occurrences - PostgreSQL
DESCRIPTION: This SQL statement counts the number of rows in a specified table where a specified column contains the invalid Unicode character '\u0000'. Replace `TableName` and `ColumnName` with the actual table and column names identified in the error message. This helps in identifying the scope of the problem before attempting to fix the data.
