TITLE: Creating Retention IDs Table SQL
DESCRIPTION: This SQL script creates the `retentionidsfordeletion` table if it doesn't already exist. It includes the `id` as the primary key, `tablename` to identify the table associated with the IDs, and `ids` as an array of IDs.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mattermost/docs/blob/master/source/upgrade/important-upgrade-notes.rst#_snippet_26

LANGUAGE: SQL
CODE:
```
CREATE TABLE
IF NOT EXISTS
  retentionidsfordeletion(id
    VARCHAR(26) PRIMARY KEY,
    tablename VARCHAR(64),
    ids VARCHAR(26) []);
CREATE INDEX

IF NOT EXISTS
  idx_retentionidsfordeletion_tablename
  ON retentionidsfordeletion(
    tablename);
```

