TITLE: Parse LDAP ObjectGUID in Golang
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to parse the hexadecimal representation of an Active Directory ObjectGUID (as emitted by the go-ldap library) into a base-10 representation. It iterates through the hexadecimal byte array and prints the integer value of each byte.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mattermost/docs/blob/master/source/onboard/sso-saml-technical.rst#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
package main

import (
	"fmt"
)

func main() {
	// Example ObjectGUID as hexadecimal byte array with backslashes
	objectGUID := "\1e\bc\ff\1e\a3\4a\9d\4f\a5\08\d4\d8\1f\1f\58\73"

	// Remove backslashes and convert to a slice of bytes (you'd need to implement this)
	// For simplicity, let's assume we have the byte slice directly.
	// In reality you would need to decode the hex string into a byte slice.
	guidBytes := []byte{30, 188, 255, 30, 163, 74, 157, 79, 165, 8, 212, 216, 31, 31, 88, 115}

	// Print the base 10 representation of each byte
	fmt.Print("[")
	for i, b := range guidBytes {
		fmt.Print(b)
		if i < len(guidBytes)-1 {
			fmt.Print(" ")
		}
	}
	fmt.Println("]")
}

```

