TITLE: Counting OAuth Data Rows MySQL
DESCRIPTION: This SQL query counts the number of rows in the `OAuthAccessData` table that do not have corresponding entries in the `Preferences` table, joined with the `Sessions` table on the token. This helps determine the number of OAuth access data entries potentially impacted by changes or deletions, specifically in MySQL environments. It uses `LEFT JOIN` and `INNER JOIN` clauses, with a `WHERE p.name IS NULL` to identify rows without corresponding preferences.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mattermost/docs/blob/master/source/upgrade/important-upgrade-notes.rst#_snippet_22

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
 SELECT COUNT(o.`Token`)
 FROM OAuthAccessData o
 LEFT JOIN Preferences p ON o.
   clientid = p.name
   AND o.userid = p.userid
   AND p.category = 'oauth_app'
 INNER JOIN Sessions s ON o.token = s
   .token
 WHERE p.name IS NULL;
```

