TITLE: Securing Private Key with Password - Bash
DESCRIPTION: This command secures the private key (`mattermost-x509.key`) using `openssl pkcs8` and the DES3 encryption algorithm. The resulting encrypted key is saved as `mattermost-x509.secure.key`.  The user will be prompted for a password during the encryption process.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mattermost/docs/blob/master/source/scripts/generate-certificates/gencert.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
# secure
openssl pkcs8 -in mattermost-x509.key -topk8 -v2 des3 -out mattermost-x509.secure.key
```

