TITLE: Creating CA Certificate (OpenSSL)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet creates a certificate for the generated CA key. The certificate is valid for 365 days and contains information about the organization and domain.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mattermost/docs/blob/master/source/onboard/ssl-client-certificate.rst#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: sh
CODE:
```
openssl req -new -x509 -days 365 -key ca.mattermost.key -out ca.mattermost.crt
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Importing a GPG Key on Linux
DESCRIPTION: Imports an existing GPG key from a file. Requires GnuPG to be installed.  The /path/to/your-key.asc placeholder needs to be replaced with the actual path to the GPG key file.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mattermost/docs/blob/master/source/manage/code-signing-custom-builds.rst#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: sh
CODE:
```
gpg --import /path/to/your-key.asc
```

